parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Stripped or damaged lug nuts can cause the wheel to come loose while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential wheel separation.
symptoms: Difficulty tightening or loosening lug nuts
wheel wobbles or vibrates while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the hub assembly can cause the wheel to come loose, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential wheel separation.
symptoms: Grinding or clicking noise from the wheel hub
vibration or wobble in the wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the transmission grinds or makes unusual noises
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
